Synthesis of JUC-124:
A mixture of H12TDDPB (5 mg, 0.0039 mmol) and Zn(NO3
)2•6H2O (15 mg, 0.05 mmol) was dissolved in 
DMF-H2O (4 ml-1 ml) in a screw-capped vial. After concentrated HNO3 of 0.10 ml was added to the mixture, the 
vial was capped and placed in an oven at 85 °C for 72 h to obtain the product with the yield of 60% (based on Zn) 
as colourless crystal. Element analysis (%) Calc. for C90H90N8O26Zn3
: C, 47.81; H, 3.98; N, 4.96; Found: C, 48.13; 
H,3.82; N, 4.01.Selected FT-IR data (KBr pellet, cm-1
): 3429 (br), 3060 (s), 2800 (s), 2468 (s), 1648 (s), 1573 (s), 
1355 (s), 1095 (s), 1425 (s), 860 (s), 777 (s), 721 (s), 638 (s), 458 (s)
